** Carnage watched Teltoli's expression after she had given the fuzor the 
tiny bit of information that she had about her comings here. It was very 
interesting to see just what her reaction would be and how her mind would be 
able to try and get as much of information of what little she had offered to 
the cutting board.
Carnage nodded to Teltoli but then looked at her as if she had just 
remembered something when the fuzor spoke up of her age.
Old? OLD?!!
She glared. She was NOT old! She had just lived through a lot and that could 
ware a bot down over a bit of time.
Carnage growled.** " I'm NOT old. Just weathered." ** Her tone was almost 
flat but there was a hint of amusement in it.
She looked Teltoli over and wondered just what was ticking inside of the 
woman's head right about now? Probably something which was trying to figure 
out just how she had gotten here without just coming out and asking about 
it.
But she could wait just as long as anyone could, but the questions would 
come eventually.
Carnage sighed. Old? Slag! Leave it to a younger bot to call her that!
She had to admit, she wasn't as young and flexible as she use to be but old 
was a rather harsh way of putting it.
: Ah! Just face it! You're getting old there, girl!:
Carnage winced. She wasn't old! Just...not as young as she once was. 
Well...she wasn't in her twenties anymore...and the thirties were running 
out pretty fast. But that wasn't exactly old...it was just the prime of ones 
life. Now the sixties were old!
Carnage snickered to herself. It was kind of funny to think that she was 
thinking about this now, really wondering just how old she would have to be 
before she finally admitted that she really was losing the youth. Ah well! 
The body was one thing but the mind was another.
She shook a bit of the water off of her scales while trying to keep the pigs 
on her back at the same time, finally thinking that it was useless since the 
rain would keep following for a little while. But it was just beginning to 
get dark and she would have to find shelter for the both of them soon, maybe 
roast up one of those pigs...even though she had planned to take them back 
and store them for later on. But she knew that she knew better then to go so 
far for food that it would have to be eaten or rot before she got it back to 
the swamps. She would hunt again before she got home. **
